NXT-19085 | [Done Done] [Story] Income Surveys - Add New Survey - Students Step - Add/Find a Student
Module: Eligibility  |  components: Eligibility  |  Release Notes Required: -

## Acceptance Criteria  [TIER 1 — agreed workflow]
Verify that in the Income Survey page, when a user selects ‘Add New Survey’, the wizard page displays the Students step
Verify that the Students step contains functions to Find or Add a student
Verify those buttons function as outlined in the requirements above, through the ‘Add a Student’ function
Verify the user can locate and/or add one or more students to the survey using this function
Verify that the Students step of the survey then shows data for those students, if the user adds them
Verify that any potential household members related to (valid) students in the grid are shown and can be linked
Verify that the user can go back and edit (new) students or remove the students they’ve added as well
Verify that the students that the user adds on this step are retained if the user proceeds to the next step and then goes back to this previous step, or vice-versa

## Release Notes  [TIER 1 — customer-facing voice]
(empty)

## Description  [TIER 3 — lowest trust, often pre-scope]
As a district admin, I would like the ability to quickly and easily add one or more students to a manual income survey on behalf of a household, so that their income data is entered into our system for reference at any time.
Summary
Add the ‘Add a Student’ pop-up to the Student step that allows users to find or add students to a new survey.
Requirements
Continued from . 

Finding a student
Using the search field, allow a user to type a student’s details (combinations of first, last, ID) 

Display the 10 most related student records and allow the user to add student(s) to the survey 

No categorical question needed

No income question needed



Adding a student
Using the drawer, implement the same ‘Add a Student’ functionality as is used within the Forms > Applications > Add Application wizard. 

When the user enters at least the First Name and Last Name and clicks ‘Add’, add the student to the survey.

No categorical question needed

No income question needed



Display the list of added students in a grid
We don’t need to warn if the student is DC, etc. like with the application

However, we should continue offering to link the student to other students who are potential household members (see concept image #3) if they exist.

Pending students should display an ‘edit’ pencil that opens an ‘Edit Student’ drawer (not pictured in mock-up), which the user can use to edit that students details. This is for pending students only.

There should be a trash bin icon which the user can use to remove a student.



This story is complete when a user can use the search field or ‘add’ drawer to search for an existing student or add a new one, and then be able to add the student to their survey successfully, also being given the option to link potential household member students if they exist. Finally, they should also be able to go back and edit pending student details as well as remove students from their survey.


